# ALFALAH APP

ALFALAH APP is a modular Islamic companion application built in C++ that helps users track prayer times, manage locations, and access daily prayer-related functionality through a structured backend system powered by SQLite.

The project focuses on clean architecture, scalability, and maintainable object-oriented design.

---

# Features

* User management system
* Prayer time tracking
* Next prayer countdown
* Location management
* SQLite database integration
* Modular C++ architecture
* Makefile build system
* Scalable backend structure
* Git-based collaborative development workflow

---

# Technologies Used

* C++
* SQLite3
* Makefile
* Git & GitHub

---

# Project Structure

```bash
ALFALAH-APP/
│
├── src/
│   ├── main.cpp
│   ├── user.cpp
│   ├── database.cpp
│   ├── location.cpp
│   ├── prayertime.cpp
│   └── README.md
│
├── headers/
│   ├── user.h
│   ├── database.h
│   ├── location.h
│   ├── prayertime.h
│   └── README.md
│
├── database/
│   ├── schema.sql
│   ├── alfalah.db
│   └── README.md
│
├── docs/
│   └── README.md
│
├── tests/
│   └── README.md
│
├── Makefile
├── .gitignore
└── README.md
```

---

# Core Modules

## User Module

Responsible for:

* User creation
* User information management
* Storing last known location
* Authentication-related functionality

---

## Database Module

Handles:

* SQLite database connection
* Query execution
* Database initialization
* Data persistence

---

## Location Module

Responsible for:

* Saving user locations
* Updating location information
* Managing location history

---

## Prayer Time Module

Handles:

* Prayer time retrieval
* Prayer schedule processing
* Next prayer countdown calculations
* Prayer time utilities

---

# Build Instructions

Compile the project using:

```bash
make
```

Clean build files:

```bash
make clean
```

---

# Running the Application

After building the project:

```bash
./app
```

The executable name may vary depending on the Makefile configuration.

---

# Database

The application uses SQLite for persistent data storage.

Example tables:

* users
* locations
* prayer_times

Database scripts and initialization files are located inside the `database/` directory.

